# vonvillas.com GitHub Notes

Reference notes for working with the vonvillas.com website repo, so we stop
re-discovering the same things.

## Two separate repos — don't mix them up

- **`edzhurai/vonvillas.com`** — the actual public website (GitHub Pages).
  Plain static HTML files. This is what serves `https://vonvillas.com`.
  Custom domain configured via a `CNAME` file in the repo root containing
  `vonvillas.com`.
- **`vvproj`** (local: `~/Dropbox/AI/vvproj`) — the Next.js/Supabase studio
  management app, deployed on **Vercel**, not GitHub Pages. Completely
  separate deployment. Claude Code has local access to this one; it does
  **not** have access to the `vonvillas.com` repo.

If a task is "add/change a page on the public website," it belongs in the
`vonvillas.com` repo, done through GitHub's web UI (see below) — not
through Claude Code, not through `vvproj`.

## Adding a file (upload)

No local checkout needed — just use the web UI:

1. Go to `github.com/edzhurai/vonvillas.com`
2. Click the **"+"** dropdown near the top right → **"Upload files"**
3. Drag the file in
4. Scroll down, commit directly to `main`

Live at `https://vonvillas.com/<filename>` within a minute or two
(GitHub Pages rebuilds automatically).

## Deleting a file

The trash-can icon in the file view is unreliable — it's been missing or
greyed out more than once. The **reliable method** is a direct URL:

```
https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/delete/<branch>/<path-to-file>
```

Example for this repo:
```
https://github.com/edzhurai/vonvillas.com/delete/main/sms.html
```

This goes straight to a delete confirmation screen with a commit box —
skips all the menu-hunting. Double-check the exact repo name and branch
from the address bar first if unsure (repo name turned out to be
`vonvillas.com`, not `edzhurai.github.io`, which caused a 404 once).

## DNS / HTTPS (Namecheap → GitHub Pages)

Already set up and confirmed working (as of July 2026):

- Four `A` records on `@` pointing to GitHub Pages' IPs:
  `185.199.108.153`, `.109.153`, `.110.153`, `.111.153`
- `CNAME` record on `www` → `edzhurai.github.io.`
- No CAA record needed (none present, and that's fine — absence doesn't
  block Let's Encrypt)
- If "Enforce HTTPS" / custom domain looks stuck on GitHub's Settings →
  Pages screen, it's often just a **stale UI render**, not an actual
  backend problem — try a plain refresh (not hard-refresh) or reopening
  the Settings → Pages tab fresh before assuming something's broken.
  Confirmed once that "DNS check in progress" was stale display, not a
  real hang.

## Current pages on the site

- `privacy.html` — privacy policy, written for Twilio A2P 10DLC compliance
  (states mobile numbers aren't shared with third parties)
- `terms.html` — SMS program terms and conditions
- `sms-consent.html` — hosted public evidence of both opt-in methods
  (verbal script + text-to-START), added for Twilio campaign review after
  a rejection (error 30909) for lacking public proof of verbal consent
- `sms.html` — **deleted** (July 2026); was a stale early draft with an old
  phone number, a home address, and inconsistent frequency claims.
  Superseded by `sms-consent.html`.

## Twilio-specific gotcha worth remembering

Verbal/offline opt-in isn't verifiable by a campaign reviewer just by
visiting the site — it needs a **hosted page describing the actual consent
script/flow** as public evidence, not just a paragraph in the
`message_flow` field describing it abstractly. This is what
`sms-consent.html` is for.